how can isee where my conversions are coming from ?

To see where your conversions are coming from, you can use the reporting section in Newsbreak Ads. This section allows you to run detailed reports on your ad performance, including conversion data. You can create custom reports and leverage audience insights to understand which creatives and audiences are driving the best results. For more information, check out our article on Reporting Conversions for CPC and CPM Campaigns: [Reporting Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/27582069096461-Reporting-Conversions-for-CPC-and-CPM-Campaigns).
my taget cpa ads arent spending budget and i do not want to increase bit because i will lose profit

If your target CPA ads aren't spending the budget, there are a few things you can check without increasing your bid:

1. **Campaign Start Date**: Ensure your campaign has started and is active.
2. **Targeting Settings**: Review your audience targeting to ensure it's not too narrow.
3. **Ad Scheduling**: Make sure your ads are scheduled to run during peak hours when your target audience is most active.
4. **Ad Creativity**: Invest in visually compelling ad content that resonates with your audience.
5. **Testing**: Run A/B tests to identify which ad variations perform best before allocating more budget.

For more detailed guidance, you can refer to our article on NewsBreak Advertising Cost: [Advertising Cost Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17959734533005-NewsBreak-Advertising-Cost).
whats the average cpa bid on target cpa

The average CPA bid on Target CPA can vary depending on your industry, audience, and campaign goals. However, it's recommended to set your bid at the highest amount you're willing to pay for a conversion. Additionally, ensure your daily budget is at least 10x your tCPA goal to allow optimal performance. For more detailed best practices on setting up Target CPA campaigns, you can check out our article: [tCPA Best Practices](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18020232662797-tCPA-Best-Practices).
